# Supabase Query Optimization

Queries must prioritize efficiency.

Filtering must happen in Supabase.

Bad:
fetch all rows then filter in JS

Good:

supabase
  .from('cards')
  .select('id,title')
  .eq('user_id', userId)

Never use select('*') unless necessary.

Always limit results.

Example:
.range(0,20)

Prefer indexed columns:
id
user_id
created_at

Avoid N+1 queries.